title: Fisher Packing Company Recalls Ready-To-Eat Pork Products Due to Possible Listeria Contamination
summary: WASHINGTON, Sept. 28, 2019 Fisher Packing Company, a Redkey, Ind. establishment, is recalling approximately 744 pounds of ready-to-eat (RTE) pork products that may be adulterated with Listeria monocytogenes, the U.S. Department of Agricultures Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced today.
